edu.udel.cis.vsl.sarl.util

Class FastList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.udel.cis.vsl.sarl.util.FastList<T>

  • public class FastList<T>
extends java.lang.Object

    An efficient doubly-linked list. What the standard Java collections are missing is the ability to concatenate two lists in constant time. You can do that here using method append(FastList).

    This class uses class FastNode to represent the nodes in the list. Each FastNode contains a reference to the contents of the node, and references to the next and previous nodes.

    There are methods to get the first and last nodes. The rest of the nodes of the list can be obtained by the methods FastNode.getNext() and FastNode.getPrev().

      • addAll

        public void addAll(T... values)
        Adds a sequence of elements to the end (back) of this list. The elements will be appended to the back of this list in the order in which they occur. Hence if the original list is L, and the arguments are v0,v1, ..., the new list will have the form L,v0,v1,....
        Parameters:
        values - any non-null sequence of elements of T. The sequence may be empty.
